81 /// expanded, promoted and normal instructions. ----
82 void NVPTXDAGToDAGISel::Select(SDNode *N) { 0
83 ----
84 if (N->isMachineOpcode()) { 0
85 N->setNodeId(-1); 0
86 return; // Already selected. 0
87 } ----
88 ----

459 case NVPTXISD::Suld2DI64Zero: ----
460 case NVPTXISD::Suld2DV2I8Zero: ----
461 case NVPTXISD::Suld2DV2I16Zero: ----
462 case NVPTXISD::Suld2DV2I32Zero: ----
463 case NVPTXISD::Suld2DV2I64Zero: ----
464 case NVPTXISD::Suld2DV4I8Zero: ----
465 case NVPTXISD::Suld2DV4I16Zero: ----
466 case NVPTXISD::Suld2DV4I32Zero: ----
467 case NVPTXISD::Suld2DArrayI8Zero: ----
468 case NVPTXISD::Suld2DArrayI16Zero: ----
469 case NVPTXISD::Suld2DArrayI32Zero: ----
470 case NVPTXISD::Suld2DArrayI64Zero: ----
471 case NVPTXISD::Suld2DArrayV2I8Zero: ----
472 case NVPTXISD::Suld2DArrayV2I16Zero: ----
473 case NVPTXISD::Suld2DArrayV2I32Zero: ----
474 case NVPTXISD::Suld2DArrayV2I64Zero: ----
475 case NVPTXISD::Suld2DArrayV4I8Zero: ----
476 case NVPTXISD::Suld2DArrayV4I16Zero: ----
477 case NVPTXISD::Suld2DArrayV4I32Zero: ----
478 case NVPTXISD::Suld3DI8Zero: ----
479 case NVPTXISD::Suld3DI16Zero: ----
480 case NVPTXISD::Suld3DI32Zero: ----
481 case NVPTXISD::Suld3DI64Zero: ----
482 case NVPTXISD::Suld3DV2I8Zero: ----
483 case NVPTXISD::Suld3DV2I16Zero: ----
484 case NVPTXISD::Suld3DV2I32Zero: ----
485 case NVPTXISD::Suld3DV2I64Zero: ----
486 case NVPTXISD::Suld3DV4I8Zero: ----
487 case NVPTXISD::Suld3DV4I16Zero: ----
488 case NVPTXISD::Suld3DV4I32Zero: ----
489 if (trySurfaceIntrinsic(N)) 0
490 return; 0
491 break; 0
492 case ISD::AND: 0
493 case ISD::SRA: ----
494 case ISD::SRL: ----
495 // Try to select BFE ----
496 if (tryBFE(N)) 0
497 return; 0
498 break; 0
499 case ISD::ADDRSPACECAST: 0
500 SelectAddrSpaceCast(N); 0
501 return; 0
502 case ISD::ConstantFP: 0
503 if (tryConstantFP(N)) 0
504 return; 0
505 break; 0
506 default: 0
507 break; 0
508 } ----
509 SelectCode(N); 0
510 } ----
511 ----
512 bool NVPTXDAGToDAGISel::tryIntrinsicChain(SDNode *N) { 0
513 unsigned IID = cast(N->getOperand(1))->getZExtValue(); 0
514 switch (IID) { 0
515 default: 0
516 return false; 0
517 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldg_global_f: 0
518 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldg_global_i: ----
519 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldg_global_p: ----
520 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldu_global_f: ----
521 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldu_global_i: ----
522 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldu_global_p: ----
523 return tryLDGLDU(N); 0
524 } ----
525 } ----
526 ----
527 // There's no way to specify FP16 and BF16 immediates in .(b)f16 ops, so we ----
528 // have to load them into an .(b)f16 register first. ----
529 bool NVPTXDAGToDAGISel::tryConstantFP(SDNode *N) { 0
530 if (N->getValueType(0) != MVT::f16 && N->getValueType(0) != MVT::bf16) 0
531 return false; 0
532 SDValue Val = CurDAG->getTargetConstantFP( 0
533 cast(N)->getValueAPF(), SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0)); 0
534 SDNode *LoadConstF16 = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
535 (N->getValueType(0) == MVT::f16 ? NVPTX::LOAD_CONST_F16 0
536 : NVPTX::LOAD_CONST_BF16), ----
537 SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0), Val); 0
538 ReplaceNode(N, LoadConstF16); 0
539 return true; 0
540 } ----
541 ----
542 // Map ISD:CONDCODE value to appropriate CmpMode expected by ----
543 // NVPTXInstPrinter::printCmpMode() ----
544 static unsigned getPTXCmpMode(const CondCodeSDNode &CondCode, bool FTZ) { 0
545 using NVPTX::PTXCmpMode::CmpMode; ----
546 unsigned PTXCmpMode = [](ISD::CondCode CC) { 0
547 switch (CC) { 0
548 default: 0
549 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected condition code."); 0
550 case ISD::SETOEQ: 0
551 return CmpMode::EQ; 0
552 case ISD::SETOGT: 0
553 return CmpMode::GT; 0
554 case ISD::SETOGE: 0
555 return CmpMode::GE; 0
556 case ISD::SETOLT: 0
557 return CmpMode::LT; 0
558 case ISD::SETOLE: 0
559 return CmpMode::LE; 0
560 case ISD::SETONE: 0
561 return CmpMode::NE; 0
562 case ISD::SETO: 0
563 return CmpMode::NUM; 0
564 case ISD::SETUO: 0
565 return CmpMode::NotANumber; 0
566 case ISD::SETUEQ: 0
567 return CmpMode::EQU; 0
568 case ISD::SETUGT: 0
569 return CmpMode::GTU; 0
570 case ISD::SETUGE: 0
571 return CmpMode::GEU; 0
572 case ISD::SETULT: 0
573 return CmpMode::LTU; 0
574 case ISD::SETULE: 0
575 return CmpMode::LEU; 0
576 case ISD::SETUNE: 0
577 return CmpMode::NEU; 0
578 case ISD::SETEQ: 0
579 return CmpMode::EQ; 0
580 case ISD::SETGT: 0
581 return CmpMode::GT; 0
582 case ISD::SETGE: 0
583 return CmpMode::GE; 0
584 case ISD::SETLT: 0
585 return CmpMode::LT; 0
586 case ISD::SETLE: 0
587 return CmpMode::LE; 0
588 case ISD::SETNE: 0
589 return CmpMode::NE; 0
590 } ----
591 }(CondCode.get()); 0
592 ----
593 if (FTZ) 0
594 PTXCmpMode |= NVPTX::PTXCmpMode::FTZ_FLAG; 0
595 ----
596 return PTXCmpMode; 0
597 } ----
598 ----
599 bool NVPTXDAGToDAGISel::SelectSETP_F16X2(SDNode *N) { 0
600 unsigned PTXCmpMode = ----
601 getPTXCmpMode(*cast(N->getOperand(2)), useF32FTZ()); 0
602 SDLoc DL(N); 0
603 SDNode *SetP = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
604 NVPTX::SETP_f16x2rr, DL, MVT::i1, MVT::i1, N->getOperand(0), 0
605 N->getOperand(1), CurDAG->getTargetConstant(PTXCmpMode, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
606 ReplaceNode(N, SetP); 0
607 return true; 0
608 } 0
609 ----
610 // Find all instances of extract_vector_elt that use this v2f16 vector ----
611 // and coalesce them into a scattering move instruction. ----
612 bool NVPTXDAGToDAGISel::tryEXTRACT_VECTOR_ELEMENT(SDNode *N) { 0
613 SDValue Vector = N->getOperand(0); 0
614 ----
615 // We only care about f16x2 as it's the only real vector type we ----
616 // need to deal with. ----
617 MVT VT = Vector.getSimpleValueType(); 0
618 if (!(VT == MVT::v2f16 || VT == MVT::v2bf16)) 0
619 return false; 0
620 // Find and record all uses of this vector that extract element 0 or 1. ----
621 SmallVector E0, E1; 0
622 for (auto *U : Vector.getNode()->uses()) { 0
623 if (U->getOpcode() != ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT) 0
624 continue; 0
625 if (U->getOperand(0) != Vector) 0
626 continue; 0
627 if (const ConstantSDNode *IdxConst = 0
628 dyn_cast(U->getOperand(1))) { 0
629 if (IdxConst->getZExtValue() == 0) 0
630 E0.push_back(U); 0
631 else if (IdxConst->getZExtValue() == 1) 0
632 E1.push_back(U); 0
633 else ----
634 llvm_unreachable("Invalid vector index."); 0
635 } ----
636 } ----
637 ----
638 // There's no point scattering f16x2 if we only ever access one ----
639 // element of it. ----
640 if (E0.empty() || E1.empty()) 0
641 return false; 0
642 ----
643 // Merge (f16 extractelt(V, 0), f16 extractelt(V,1)) ----
644 // into f16,f16 SplitF16x2(V) ----
645 MVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType(); 0
646 SDNode *ScatterOp = ----
647 CurDAG->getMachineNode(NVPTX::I32toV2I16, SDLoc(N), EltVT, EltVT, Vector); 0
648 for (auto *Node : E0) 0
649 ReplaceUses(SDValue(Node, 0), SDValue(ScatterOp, 0)); 0
650 for (auto *Node : E1) 0
651 ReplaceUses(SDValue(Node, 0), SDValue(ScatterOp, 1)); 0
652 ----
653 return true; 0
654 } 0
655 ----
656 static unsigned int getCodeAddrSpace(MemSDNode *N) { 0
657 const Value *Src = N->getMemOperand()->getValue(); 0
658 ----
659 if (!Src) 0
660 return NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::GENERIC; 0
661 ----
662 if (auto *PT = dyn_cast(Src->getType())) { 0
663 switch (PT->getAddressSpace()) { 0
664 case llvm::ADDRESS_SPACE_LOCAL: return NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::LOCAL; 0
665 case llvm::ADDRESS_SPACE_GLOBAL: return NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::GLOBAL; 0
666 case llvm::ADDRESS_SPACE_SHARED: return NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::SHARED; 0
667 case llvm::ADDRESS_SPACE_GENERIC: return NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::GENERIC; 0
668 case llvm::ADDRESS_SPACE_PARAM: return NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::PARAM; 0
669 case llvm::ADDRESS_SPACE_CONST: return NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::CONSTANT; 0
670 default: break; 0
671 } ----
672 } ----
673 return NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::GENERIC; 0
674 } ----
675 ----
676 static bool canLowerToLDG(MemSDNode *N, const NVPTXSubtarget &Subtarget, 0
677 unsigned CodeAddrSpace, MachineFunction *F) { ----
678 // We use ldg (i.e. ld.global.nc) for invariant loads from the global address ----
679 // space. ----
680 // ----
681 // We have two ways of identifying invariant loads: Loads may be explicitly ----
682 // marked as invariant, or we may infer them to be invariant. ----
683 // ----
684 // We currently infer invariance for loads from ----
685 // - constant global variables, and ----
686 // - kernel function pointer params that are noalias (i.e. __restrict) and ----
687 // never written to. ----
688 // ----
689 // TODO: Perform a more powerful invariance analysis (ideally IPO, and ideally ----
690 // not during the SelectionDAG phase). ----
691 // ----
692 // TODO: Infer invariance only at -O2. We still want to use ldg at -O0 for ----
693 // explicitly invariant loads because these are how clang tells us to use ldg ----
694 // when the user uses a builtin. ----
695 if (!Subtarget.hasLDG() || CodeAddrSpace != NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::GLOBAL) 0
696 return false; 0
697 ----
698 if (N->isInvariant()) 0
699 return true; 0
700 ----
701 bool IsKernelFn = isKernelFunction(F->getFunction()); 0
702 ----
703 // We use getUnderlyingObjects() here instead of getUnderlyingObject() mainly ----
704 // because the former looks through phi nodes while the latter does not. We ----
705 // need to look through phi nodes to handle pointer induction variables. ----
706 SmallVector Objs; 0
707 getUnderlyingObjects(N->getMemOperand()->getValue(), Objs); 0
708 ----
709 return all_of(Objs, [&](const Value *V) { 0
710 if (auto *A = dyn_cast(V)) 0
711 return IsKernelFn && A->onlyReadsMemory() && A->hasNoAliasAttr(); 0
712 if (auto *GV = dyn_cast(V)) 0
713 return GV->isConstant(); 0
714 return false; 0
715 }); 0
716 } 0
717 ----
718 bool NVPTXDAGToDAGISel::tryIntrinsicNoChain(SDNode *N) { 0
719 unsigned IID = cast(N->getOperand(0))->getZExtValue(); 0
720 switch (IID) { 0
721 default: 0
722 return false; 0
723 case Intrinsic::nvvm_texsurf_handle_internal: 0
724 SelectTexSurfHandle(N); 0
725 return true; 0
726 } ----
727 } ----
728 ----
729 void NVPTXDAGToDAGISel::SelectTexSurfHandle(SDNode *N) { 0
730 // Op 0 is the intrinsic ID ----
731 SDValue Wrapper = N->getOperand(1); 0
732 SDValue GlobalVal = Wrapper.getOperand(0); 0
733 ReplaceNode(N, CurDAG->getMachineNode(NVPTX::texsurf_handles, SDLoc(N), 0
734 MVT::i64, GlobalVal)); ----
735 } 0
736 ----
737 void NVPTXDAGToDAGISel::SelectAddrSpaceCast(SDNode *N) { 0
738 SDValue Src = N->getOperand(0); 0
739 AddrSpaceCastSDNode *CastN = cast(N); 0
740 unsigned SrcAddrSpace = CastN->getSrcAddressSpace(); 0
741 unsigned DstAddrSpace = CastN->getDestAddressSpace(); 0
742 assert(SrcAddrSpace != DstAddrSpace && 0
743 "addrspacecast must be between different address spaces"); ----
744 ----
745 if (DstAddrSpace == ADDRESS_SPACE_GENERIC) { 0
746 // Specific to generic ----
747 unsigned Opc; ----
748 switch (SrcAddrSpace) { 0
749 default: report_fatal_error("Bad address space in addrspacecast"); 0
750 case ADDRESS_SPACE_GLOBAL: 0
751 Opc = TM.is64Bit() ? NVPTX::cvta_global_yes_64 : NVPTX::cvta_global_yes; 0
752 break; 0
753 case ADDRESS_SPACE_SHARED: 0
754 Opc = TM.is64Bit() ? (useShortPointers() ? NVPTX::cvta_shared_yes_6432 0
755 : NVPTX::cvta_shared_yes_64) ----
756 : NVPTX::cvta_shared_yes; ----
757 break; 0
758 case ADDRESS_SPACE_CONST: 0
759 Opc = TM.is64Bit() ? (useShortPointers() ? NVPTX::cvta_const_yes_6432 0
760 : NVPTX::cvta_const_yes_64) ----
761 : NVPTX::cvta_const_yes; ----
762 break; 0
763 case ADDRESS_SPACE_LOCAL: 0
764 Opc = TM.is64Bit() ? (useShortPointers() ? NVPTX::cvta_local_yes_6432 0
765 : NVPTX::cvta_local_yes_64) ----
766 : NVPTX::cvta_local_yes; ----
767 break; 0
768 } ----
769 ReplaceNode(N, CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opc, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0), 0
770 Src)); ----
771 return; 0
772 } else { ----
773 // Generic to specific ----
774 if (SrcAddrSpace != 0) 0
775 report_fatal_error("Cannot cast between two non-generic address spaces"); 0
776 unsigned Opc; ----
777 switch (DstAddrSpace) { 0
778 default: report_fatal_error("Bad address space in addrspacecast"); 0
779 case ADDRESS_SPACE_GLOBAL: 0
780 Opc = TM.is64Bit() ? NVPTX::cvta_to_global_yes_64 0
781 : NVPTX::cvta_to_global_yes; ----
782 break; 0
783 case ADDRESS_SPACE_SHARED: 0
784 Opc = TM.is64Bit() ? (useShortPointers() ? NVPTX::cvta_to_shared_yes_3264 0
785 : NVPTX::cvta_to_shared_yes_64) ----
786 : NVPTX::cvta_to_shared_yes; ----
787 break; 0
788 case ADDRESS_SPACE_CONST: 0
789 Opc = TM.is64Bit() ? (useShortPointers() ? NVPTX::cvta_to_const_yes_3264 0
790 : NVPTX::cvta_to_const_yes_64) ----
791 : NVPTX::cvta_to_const_yes; ----
792 break; 0
793 case ADDRESS_SPACE_LOCAL: 0
794 Opc = TM.is64Bit() ? (useShortPointers() ? NVPTX::cvta_to_local_yes_3264 0
795 : NVPTX::cvta_to_local_yes_64) ----
796 : NVPTX::cvta_to_local_yes; ----
797 break; 0
798 case ADDRESS_SPACE_PARAM: 0
799 Opc = TM.is64Bit() ? NVPTX::nvvm_ptr_gen_to_param_64 0
800 : NVPTX::nvvm_ptr_gen_to_param; ----
801 break; 0
802 } ----
803 ReplaceNode(N, CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opc, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0), 0
804 Src)); ----
805 return; 0
806 } ----
807 } ----
808 ----
809 // Helper function template to reduce amount of boilerplate code for ----
810 // opcode selection. ----
811 static std::optional ----
812 pickOpcodeForVT(MVT::SimpleValueType VT, unsigned Opcode_i8, 0
813 unsigned Opcode_i16, unsigned Opcode_i32, ----
814 std::optional Opcode_i64, unsigned Opcode_f32, ----
815 std::optional Opcode_f64) { ----
816 switch (VT) { 0
817 case MVT::i1: 0
818 case MVT::i8: ----
819 return Opcode_i8; 0
820 case MVT::i16: 0
821 return Opcode_i16; 0
822 case MVT::i32: 0
823 return Opcode_i32; 0
824 case MVT::i64: 0
825 return Opcode_i64; 0
826 case MVT::f16: 0
827 case MVT::bf16: ----
828 return Opcode_i16; 0
829 case MVT::v2f16: 0
830 case MVT::v2bf16: ----
831 return Opcode_i32; 0
832 case MVT::f32: 0
833 return Opcode_f32; 0
834 case MVT::f64: 0
835 return Opcode_f64; 0
836 default: 0
837 return std::nullopt; 0
838 } ----
839 } ----
840 ----
841 static int getLdStRegType(EVT VT) { 0
842 if (VT.isFloatingPoint()) 0
843 switch (VT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy) { 0
844 case MVT::f16: 0
845 case MVT::bf16: ----
846 case MVT::v2f16: ----
847 case MVT::v2bf16: ----
848 return NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::Untyped; 0
849 default: 0
850 return NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::Float; 0
851 } ----
852 else ----
853 return NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::Unsigned; 0
854 } ----
855 ----
856 bool NVPTXDAGToDAGISel::tryLoad(SDNode *N) { 0
857 SDLoc dl(N); 0
858 MemSDNode *LD = cast(N); 0
859 assert(LD->readMem() && "Expected load"); 0
860 LoadSDNode *PlainLoad = dyn_cast(N); 0
861 EVT LoadedVT = LD->getMemoryVT(); 0
862 SDNode *NVPTXLD = nullptr; 0
863 ----
864 // do not support pre/post inc/dec ----
865 if (PlainLoad && PlainLoad->isIndexed()) 0
866 return false; 0
867 ----
868 if (!LoadedVT.isSimple()) 0
869 return false; 0
870 ----
871 AtomicOrdering Ordering = LD->getSuccessOrdering(); 0
872 // In order to lower atomic loads with stronger guarantees we would need to ----
873 // use load.acquire or insert fences. However these features were only added ----
874 // with PTX ISA 6.0 / sm_70. ----
875 // TODO: Check if we can actually use the new instructions and implement them. ----
876 if (isStrongerThanMonotonic(Ordering)) 0
877 return false; 0
878 ----
879 // Address Space Setting ----
880 unsigned int CodeAddrSpace = getCodeAddrSpace(LD); 0
881 if (canLowerToLDG(LD, *Subtarget, CodeAddrSpace, MF)) { 0
882 return tryLDGLDU(N); 0
883 } ----
884 ----
885 unsigned int PointerSize = ----
886 CurDAG->getDataLayout().getPointerSizeInBits(LD->getAddressSpace()); 0
887 ----
888 // Volatile Setting ----
889 // - .volatile is only available for .global and .shared ----
890 // - .volatile has the same memory synchronization semantics as .relaxed.sys ----
891 bool isVolatile = LD->isVolatile() || Ordering == AtomicOrdering::Monotonic; 0
892 if (CodeAddrSpace != NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::GLOBAL && 0
893 CodeAddrSpace != NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::SHARED && 0
894 CodeAddrSpace != NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::GENERIC) ----
895 isVolatile = false; 0
896 ----
897 // Type Setting: fromType + fromTypeWidth ----
898 // ----
899 // Sign : ISD::SEXTLOAD ----
900 // Unsign : ISD::ZEXTLOAD, ISD::NON_EXTLOAD or ISD::EXTLOAD and the ----
901 // type is integer ----
902 // Float : ISD::NON_EXTLOAD or ISD::EXTLOAD and the type is float ----
903 MVT SimpleVT = LoadedVT.getSimpleVT(); 0
904 MVT ScalarVT = SimpleVT.getScalarType(); 0
905 // Read at least 8 bits (predicates are stored as 8-bit values) ----
906 unsigned fromTypeWidth = std::max(8U, (unsigned)ScalarVT.getSizeInBits()); 0
907 unsigned int fromType; ----
908 ----
909 // Vector Setting ----
910 unsigned vecType = NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::Scalar; 0
911 if (SimpleVT.isVector()) { 0
912 assert((LoadedVT == MVT::v2f16 || LoadedVT == MVT::v2bf16) && 0
913 "Unexpected vector type"); ----
914 // v2f16/v2bf16 is loaded using ld.b32 ----
915 fromTypeWidth = 32; 0
916 } ----
917 ----
918 if (PlainLoad && (PlainLoad->getExtensionType() == ISD::SEXTLOAD)) 0
919 fromType = NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::Signed; 0
920 else ----
921 fromType = getLdStRegType(ScalarVT); 0
922 ----
923 // Create the machine instruction DAG ----
924 SDValue Chain = N->getOperand(0); 0
925 SDValue N1 = N->getOperand(1); 0
926 SDValue Addr; 0
927 SDValue Offset, Base; 0
928 std::optional Opcode; 0
929 MVT::SimpleValueType TargetVT = LD->getSimpleValueType(0).SimpleTy; 0
930 ----
931 if (SelectDirectAddr(N1, Addr)) { 0
932 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(TargetVT, NVPTX::LD_i8_avar, NVPTX::LD_i16_avar, 0
933 NVPTX::LD_i32_avar, NVPTX::LD_i64_avar, 0
934 NVPTX::LD_f32_avar, NVPTX::LD_f64_avar); 0
935 if (!Opcode) 0
936 return false; 0
937 SDValue Ops[] = { getI32Imm(isVolatile, dl), getI32Imm(CodeAddrSpace, dl), 0
938 getI32Imm(vecType, dl), getI32Imm(fromType, dl), 0
939 getI32Imm(fromTypeWidth, dl), Addr, Chain }; 0
940 NVPTXLD = CurDAG->getMachineNode(*Opcode, dl, TargetVT, MVT::Other, Ops); 0
941 } else if (PointerSize == 64 ? SelectADDRsi64(N1.getNode(), N1, Base, Offset) 0
942 : SelectADDRsi(N1.getNode(), N1, Base, Offset)) { 0
943 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(TargetVT, NVPTX::LD_i8_asi, NVPTX::LD_i16_asi, 0
944 NVPTX::LD_i32_asi, NVPTX::LD_i64_asi, 0
945 NVPTX::LD_f32_asi, NVPTX::LD_f64_asi); 0
946 if (!Opcode) 0
947 return false; 0
948 SDValue Ops[] = { getI32Imm(isVolatile, dl), getI32Imm(CodeAddrSpace, dl), 0
949 getI32Imm(vecType, dl), getI32Imm(fromType, dl), 0
950 getI32Imm(fromTypeWidth, dl), Base, Offset, Chain }; 0
951 NVPTXLD = CurDAG->getMachineNode(*Opcode, dl, TargetVT, MVT::Other, Ops); 0
952 } else if (PointerSize == 64 ? SelectADDRri64(N1.getNode(), N1, Base, Offset) 0
953 : SelectADDRri(N1.getNode(), N1, Base, Offset)) { 0
954 if (PointerSize == 64) 0
955 Opcode = ----
956 pickOpcodeForVT(TargetVT, NVPTX::LD_i8_ari_64, NVPTX::LD_i16_ari_64, 0
957 NVPTX::LD_i32_ari_64, NVPTX::LD_i64_ari_64, 0
958 NVPTX::LD_f32_ari_64, NVPTX::LD_f64_ari_64); 0
959 else ----
960 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(TargetVT, NVPTX::LD_i8_ari, NVPTX::LD_i16_ari, 0
961 NVPTX::LD_i32_ari, NVPTX::LD_i64_ari, 0
962 NVPTX::LD_f32_ari, NVPTX::LD_f64_ari); 0
963 if (!Opcode) 0
964 return false; 0
965 SDValue Ops[] = { getI32Imm(isVolatile, dl), getI32Imm(CodeAddrSpace, dl), 0
966 getI32Imm(vecType, dl), getI32Imm(fromType, dl), 0
967 getI32Imm(fromTypeWidth, dl), Base, Offset, Chain }; 0
968 NVPTXLD = CurDAG->getMachineNode(*Opcode, dl, TargetVT, MVT::Other, Ops); 0
969 } else { ----
970 if (PointerSize == 64) 0
971 Opcode = ----
972 pickOpcodeForVT(TargetVT, NVPTX::LD_i8_areg_64, NVPTX::LD_i16_areg_64, 0
973 NVPTX::LD_i32_areg_64, NVPTX::LD_i64_areg_64, 0
974 NVPTX::LD_f32_areg_64, NVPTX::LD_f64_areg_64); 0
975 else ----
976 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(TargetVT, NVPTX::LD_i8_areg, NVPTX::LD_i16_areg, 0
977 NVPTX::LD_i32_areg, NVPTX::LD_i64_areg, 0
978 NVPTX::LD_f32_areg, NVPTX::LD_f64_areg); 0
979 if (!Opcode) 0
980 return false; 0
981 SDValue Ops[] = { getI32Imm(isVolatile, dl), getI32Imm(CodeAddrSpace, dl), 0
982 getI32Imm(vecType, dl), getI32Imm(fromType, dl), 0
983 getI32Imm(fromTypeWidth, dl), N1, Chain }; 0
984 NVPTXLD = CurDAG->getMachineNode(*Opcode, dl, TargetVT, MVT::Other, Ops); 0
985 } ----
986 ----
987 if (!NVPTXLD) 0
988 return false; 0
989 ----
990 MachineMemOperand *MemRef = cast(N)->getMemOperand(); 0
991 CurDAG->setNodeMemRefs(cast(NVPTXLD), {MemRef}); 0
992 ----
993 ReplaceNode(N, NVPTXLD); 0
994 return true; 0
995 } 0
996 ----
997 bool NVPTXDAGToDAGISel::tryLoadVector(SDNode *N) { 0
998 ----
999 SDValue Chain = N->getOperand(0); 0
1000 SDValue Op1 = N->getOperand(1); 0
1001 SDValue Addr, Offset, Base; 0
1002 std::optional Opcode; 0
1003 SDLoc DL(N); 0
1004 SDNode *LD; ----
1005 MemSDNode *MemSD = cast(N); 0
1006 EVT LoadedVT = MemSD->getMemoryVT(); 0
1007 ----
1008 if (!LoadedVT.isSimple()) 0
1009 return false; 0
1010 ----
1011 // Address Space Setting ----
1012 unsigned int CodeAddrSpace = getCodeAddrSpace(MemSD); 0
1013 if (canLowerToLDG(MemSD, *Subtarget, CodeAddrSpace, MF)) { 0
1014 return tryLDGLDU(N); 0
1015 } ----
1016 ----
1017 unsigned int PointerSize = ----
1018 CurDAG->getDataLayout().getPointerSizeInBits(MemSD->getAddressSpace()); 0
1019 ----
1020 // Volatile Setting ----
1021 // - .volatile is only availalble for .global and .shared ----
1022 bool IsVolatile = MemSD->isVolatile(); 0
1023 if (CodeAddrSpace != NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::GLOBAL && 0
1024 CodeAddrSpace != NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::SHARED && 0
1025 CodeAddrSpace != NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::GENERIC) ----
1026 IsVolatile = false; 0
1027 ----
1028 // Vector Setting ----
1029 MVT SimpleVT = LoadedVT.getSimpleVT(); 0
1030 ----
1031 // Type Setting: fromType + fromTypeWidth ----
1032 // ----
1033 // Sign : ISD::SEXTLOAD ----
1034 // Unsign : ISD::ZEXTLOAD, ISD::NON_EXTLOAD or ISD::EXTLOAD and the ----
1035 // type is integer ----
1036 // Float : ISD::NON_EXTLOAD or ISD::EXTLOAD and the type is float ----
1037 MVT ScalarVT = SimpleVT.getScalarType(); 0
1038 // Read at least 8 bits (predicates are stored as 8-bit values) ----
1039 unsigned FromTypeWidth = std::max(8U, (unsigned)ScalarVT.getSizeInBits()); 0
1040 unsigned int FromType; ----
1041 // The last operand holds the original LoadSDNode::getExtensionType() value ----
1042 unsigned ExtensionType = cast( ----
1043 N->getOperand(N->getNumOperands() - 1))->getZExtValue(); 0
1044 if (ExtensionType == ISD::SEXTLOAD) 0
1045 FromType = NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::Signed; 0
1046 else ----
1047 FromType = getLdStRegType(ScalarVT); 0
1048 ----
1049 unsigned VecType; ----
1050 ----
1051 switch (N->getOpcode()) { 0
1052 case NVPTXISD::LoadV2: 0
1053 VecType = NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::V2; 0
1054 break; 0
1055 case NVPTXISD::LoadV4: 0
1056 VecType = NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::V4; 0
1057 break; 0
1058 default: 0
1059 return false; 0
1060 } ----
1061 ----
1062 EVT EltVT = N->getValueType(0); 0
1063 ----
1064 // v8f16 is a special case. PTX doesn't have ld.v8.f16 ----
1065 // instruction. Instead, we split the vector into v2f16 chunks and ----
1066 // load them with ld.v4.b32. ----
1067 if (EltVT == MVT::v2f16 || EltVT == MVT::v2bf16) { 0
1068 assert(N->getOpcode() == NVPTXISD::LoadV4 && "Unexpected load opcode."); 0
1069 EltVT = MVT::i32; 0
1070 FromType = NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::Untyped; 0
1071 FromTypeWidth = 32; 0
1072 } ----
1073 ----
1074 if (SelectDirectAddr(Op1, Addr)) { 0
1075 switch (N->getOpcode()) { 0
1076 default: 0
1077 return false; 0
1078 case NVPTXISD::LoadV2: 0
1079 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
1080 NVPTX::LDV_i8_v2_avar, NVPTX::LDV_i16_v2_avar, ----
1081 NVPTX::LDV_i32_v2_avar, NVPTX::LDV_i64_v2_avar, 0
1082 NVPTX::LDV_f32_v2_avar, NVPTX::LDV_f64_v2_avar); 0
1083 break; 0
1084 case NVPTXISD::LoadV4: 0
1085 Opcode = ----
1086 pickOpcodeForVT(EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, NVPTX::LDV_i8_v4_avar, 0
1087 NVPTX::LDV_i16_v4_avar, NVPTX::LDV_i32_v4_avar, ----
1088 std::nullopt, NVPTX::LDV_f32_v4_avar, std::nullopt); ----
1089 break; 0
1090 } ----
1091 if (!Opcode) 0
1092 return false; 0
1093 SDValue Ops[] = { getI32Imm(IsVolatile, DL), getI32Imm(CodeAddrSpace, DL), 0
1094 getI32Imm(VecType, DL), getI32Imm(FromType, DL), 0
1095 getI32Imm(FromTypeWidth, DL), Addr, Chain }; 0
1096 LD = CurDAG->getMachineNode(*Opcode, DL, N->getVTList(), Ops); 0
1097 } else if (PointerSize == 64 0
1098 ? SelectADDRsi64(Op1.getNode(), Op1, Base, Offset) 0
1099 : SelectADDRsi(Op1.getNode(), Op1, Base, Offset)) { 0
1100 switch (N->getOpcode()) { 0
1101 default: 0
1102 return false; 0
1103 case NVPTXISD::LoadV2: 0
1104 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
1105 NVPTX::LDV_i8_v2_asi, NVPTX::LDV_i16_v2_asi, ----
1106 NVPTX::LDV_i32_v2_asi, NVPTX::LDV_i64_v2_asi, 0
1107 NVPTX::LDV_f32_v2_asi, NVPTX::LDV_f64_v2_asi); 0
1108 break; 0
1109 case NVPTXISD::LoadV4: 0
1110 Opcode = ----
1111 pickOpcodeForVT(EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, NVPTX::LDV_i8_v4_asi, 0
1112 NVPTX::LDV_i16_v4_asi, NVPTX::LDV_i32_v4_asi, ----
1113 std::nullopt, NVPTX::LDV_f32_v4_asi, std::nullopt); ----
1114 break; 0
1115 } ----
1116 if (!Opcode) 0
1117 return false; 0
1118 SDValue Ops[] = { getI32Imm(IsVolatile, DL), getI32Imm(CodeAddrSpace, DL), 0
1119 getI32Imm(VecType, DL), getI32Imm(FromType, DL), 0
1120 getI32Imm(FromTypeWidth, DL), Base, Offset, Chain }; 0
1121 LD = CurDAG->getMachineNode(*Opcode, DL, N->getVTList(), Ops); 0
1122 } else if (PointerSize == 64 0
1123 ? SelectADDRri64(Op1.getNode(), Op1, Base, Offset) 0
1124 : SelectADDRri(Op1.getNode(), Op1, Base, Offset)) { 0
1125 if (PointerSize == 64) { 0
1126 switch (N->getOpcode()) { 0
1127 default: 0
1128 return false; 0
1129 case NVPTXISD::LoadV2: 0
1130 Opcode = ----
1131 pickOpcodeForVT(EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
1132 NVPTX::LDV_i8_v2_ari_64, NVPTX::LDV_i16_v2_ari_64, ----
1133 NVPTX::LDV_i32_v2_ari_64, NVPTX::LDV_i64_v2_ari_64, 0
1134 NVPTX::LDV_f32_v2_ari_64, NVPTX::LDV_f64_v2_ari_64); 0
1135 break; 0
1136 case NVPTXISD::LoadV4: 0
1137 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT( 0
1138 EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, NVPTX::LDV_i8_v4_ari_64, 0
1139 NVPTX::LDV_i16_v4_ari_64, NVPTX::LDV_i32_v4_ari_64, std::nullopt, ----
1140 NVPTX::LDV_f32_v4_ari_64, std::nullopt); ----
1141 break; 0
1142 } ----
1143 } else { ----
1144 switch (N->getOpcode()) { 0
1145 default: 0
1146 return false; 0
1147 case NVPTXISD::LoadV2: 0
1148 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
1149 NVPTX::LDV_i8_v2_ari, NVPTX::LDV_i16_v2_ari, ----
1150 NVPTX::LDV_i32_v2_ari, NVPTX::LDV_i64_v2_ari, 0
1151 NVPTX::LDV_f32_v2_ari, NVPTX::LDV_f64_v2_ari); 0
1152 break; 0
1153 case NVPTXISD::LoadV4: 0
1154 Opcode = ----
1155 pickOpcodeForVT(EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, NVPTX::LDV_i8_v4_ari, 0
1156 NVPTX::LDV_i16_v4_ari, NVPTX::LDV_i32_v4_ari, ----
1157 std::nullopt, NVPTX::LDV_f32_v4_ari, std::nullopt); ----
1158 break; 0
1159 } ----
1160 } ----
1161 if (!Opcode) 0
1162 return false; 0
1163 SDValue Ops[] = { getI32Imm(IsVolatile, DL), getI32Imm(CodeAddrSpace, DL), 0
1164 getI32Imm(VecType, DL), getI32Imm(FromType, DL), 0
1165 getI32Imm(FromTypeWidth, DL), Base, Offset, Chain }; 0
1166 ----
1167 LD = CurDAG->getMachineNode(*Opcode, DL, N->getVTList(), Ops); 0
1168 } else { ----
1169 if (PointerSize == 64) { 0
1170 switch (N->getOpcode()) { 0
1171 default: 0
1172 return false; 0
1173 case NVPTXISD::LoadV2: 0
1174 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT( 0
1175 EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, NVPTX::LDV_i8_v2_areg_64, 0
1176 NVPTX::LDV_i16_v2_areg_64, NVPTX::LDV_i32_v2_areg_64, ----
1177 NVPTX::LDV_i64_v2_areg_64, NVPTX::LDV_f32_v2_areg_64, 0
1178 NVPTX::LDV_f64_v2_areg_64); 0
1179 break; 0
1180 case NVPTXISD::LoadV4: 0
1181 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT( 0
1182 EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, NVPTX::LDV_i8_v4_areg_64, 0
1183 NVPTX::LDV_i16_v4_areg_64, NVPTX::LDV_i32_v4_areg_64, std::nullopt, ----
1184 NVPTX::LDV_f32_v4_areg_64, std::nullopt); ----
1185 break; 0
1186 } ----
1187 } else { ----
1188 switch (N->getOpcode()) { 0
1189 default: 0
1190 return false; 0
1191 case NVPTXISD::LoadV2: 0
1192 Opcode = ----
1193 pickOpcodeForVT(EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, NVPTX::LDV_i8_v2_areg, 0
1194 NVPTX::LDV_i16_v2_areg, NVPTX::LDV_i32_v2_areg, ----
1195 NVPTX::LDV_i64_v2_areg, NVPTX::LDV_f32_v2_areg, 0
1196 NVPTX::LDV_f64_v2_areg); 0
1197 break; 0
1198 case NVPTXISD::LoadV4: 0
1199 Opcode = ----
1200 pickOpcodeForVT(EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, NVPTX::LDV_i8_v4_areg, 0
1201 NVPTX::LDV_i16_v4_areg, NVPTX::LDV_i32_v4_areg, ----
1202 std::nullopt, NVPTX::LDV_f32_v4_areg, std::nullopt); ----
1203 break; 0
1204 } ----
1205 } ----
1206 if (!Opcode) 0
1207 return false; 0
1208 SDValue Ops[] = { getI32Imm(IsVolatile, DL), getI32Imm(CodeAddrSpace, DL), 0
1209 getI32Imm(VecType, DL), getI32Imm(FromType, DL), 0
1210 getI32Imm(FromTypeWidth, DL), Op1, Chain }; 0
1211 LD = CurDAG->getMachineNode(*Opcode, DL, N->getVTList(), Ops); 0
1212 } ----
1213 ----
1214 MachineMemOperand *MemRef = cast(N)->getMemOperand(); 0
1215 CurDAG->setNodeMemRefs(cast(LD), {MemRef}); 0
1216 ----
1217 ReplaceNode(N, LD); 0
1218 return true; 0
1219 } 0
1220 ----
1221 bool NVPTXDAGToDAGISel::tryLDGLDU(SDNode *N) { 0
1222 ----
1223 SDValue Chain = N->getOperand(0); 0
1224 SDValue Op1; 0
1225 MemSDNode *Mem; ----
1226 bool IsLDG = true; 0
1227 ----
1228 // If this is an LDG intrinsic, the address is the third operand. If its an ----
1229 // LDG/LDU SD node (from custom vector handling), then its the second operand ----
1230 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN) { 0
1231 Op1 = N->getOperand(2); 0
1232 Mem = cast(N); 0
1233 unsigned IID = cast(N->getOperand(1))->getZExtValue(); 0
1234 switch (IID) { 0
1235 default: 0
1236 return false; 0
1237 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldg_global_f: 0
1238 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldg_global_i: ----
1239 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldg_global_p: ----
1240 IsLDG = true; 0
1241 break; 0
1242 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldu_global_f: 0
1243 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldu_global_i: ----
1244 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldu_global_p: ----
1245 IsLDG = false; 0
1246 break; 0
1247 } ----
1248 } else { ----
1249 Op1 = N->getOperand(1); 0
1250 Mem = cast(N); 0
1251 } ----
1252 ----
1253 std::optional Opcode; 0
1254 SDLoc DL(N); 0
1255 SDNode *LD; ----
1256 SDValue Base, Offset, Addr; 0
1257 ----
1258 EVT EltVT = Mem->getMemoryVT(); 0
1259 unsigned NumElts = 1; 0
1260 if (EltVT.isVector()) { 0
1261 NumElts = EltVT.getVectorNumElements(); 0
1262 EltVT = EltVT.getVectorElementType(); 0
1263 // vectors of f16 are loaded/stored as multiples of v2f16 elements. ----
1264 if ((EltVT == MVT::f16 && N->getValueType(0) == MVT::v2f16) || 0
1265 (EltVT == MVT::bf16 && N->getValueType(0) == MVT::v2bf16)) { 0
1266 assert(NumElts % 2 == 0 && "Vector must have even number of elements"); 0
1267 EltVT = N->getValueType(0); 0
1268 NumElts /= 2; 0
1269 } ----
1270 } ----
1271 ----
1272 // Build the "promoted" result VTList for the load. If we are really loading ----
1273 // i8s, then the return type will be promoted to i16 since we do not expose ----
1274 // 8-bit registers in NVPTX. ----
1275 EVT NodeVT = (EltVT == MVT::i8) ? MVT::i16 : EltVT; 0
1276 SmallVector InstVTs; 0
1277 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) { 0
1278 InstVTs.push_back(NodeVT); 0
1279 } ----
1280 InstVTs.push_back(MVT::Other); 0
1281 SDVTList InstVTList = CurDAG->getVTList(InstVTs); 0
1282 ----
1283 if (SelectDirectAddr(Op1, Addr)) { 0
1284 switch (N->getOpcode()) { 0
1285 default: 0
1286 return false; 0
1287 case ISD::LOAD: 0
1288 case ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN: ----
1289 if (IsLDG) 0
1290 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
1291 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_GLOBAL_i8avar, ----
1292 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_GLOBAL_i16avar, ----
1293 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_GLOBAL_i32avar, ----
1294 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_GLOBAL_i64avar, 0
1295 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_GLOBAL_f32avar, ----
1296 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_GLOBAL_f64avar); 0
1297 else ----
1298 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
1299 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_GLOBAL_i8avar, ----
1300 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_GLOBAL_i16avar, ----
1301 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_GLOBAL_i32avar, ----
1302 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_GLOBAL_i64avar, 0
1303 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_GLOBAL_f32avar, ----
1304 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_GLOBAL_f64avar); 0
1305 break; 0
1306 case NVPTXISD::LoadV2: 0
1307 case NVPTXISD::LDGV2: ----
1308 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
1309 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2i8_ELE_avar, ----
1310 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2i16_ELE_avar, ----
1311 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2i32_ELE_avar, ----
1312 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2i64_ELE_avar, 0
1313 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2f32_ELE_avar, ----
1314 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2f64_ELE_avar); 0
1315 break; 0
1316 case NVPTXISD::LDUV2: 0
1317 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
1318 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v2i8_ELE_avar, ----
1319 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v2i16_ELE_avar, ----
1320 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v2i32_ELE_avar, ----
1321 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v2i64_ELE_avar, 0
1322 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v2f32_ELE_avar, ----
1323 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v2f64_ELE_avar); 0
1324 break; 0
1325 case NVPTXISD::LoadV4: 0
1326 case NVPTXISD::LDGV4: ----
1327 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT( 0
1328 EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v4i8_ELE_avar, 0
1329 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v4i16_ELE_avar, ----
1330 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v4i32_ELE_avar, std::nullopt, ----
1331 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v4f32_ELE_avar, std::nullopt); ----
1332 break; 0
1333 case NVPTXISD::LDUV4: 0
1334 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT( 0
1335 EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v4i8_ELE_avar, 0
1336 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v4i16_ELE_avar, ----
1337 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v4i32_ELE_avar, std::nullopt, ----
1338 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v4f32_ELE_avar, std::nullopt); ----
1339 break; 0
1340 } ----
1341 if (!Opcode) 0
1342 return false; 0
1343 SDValue Ops[] = { Addr, Chain }; 0
1344 LD = CurDAG->getMachineNode(*Opcode, DL, InstVTList, Ops); 0
1345 } else if (TM.is64Bit() ? SelectADDRri64(Op1.getNode(), Op1, Base, Offset) 0
1346 : SelectADDRri(Op1.getNode(), Op1, Base, Offset)) { 0
1347 if (TM.is64Bit()) { 0
1348 switch (N->getOpcode()) { 0
1349 default: 0
1350 return false; 0
1351 case ISD::LOAD: 0

1354 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0

1356 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_GLOBAL_i16ari64, ----
1357 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_GLOBAL_i32ari64, ----
1358 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_GLOBAL_i64ari64, 0
1359 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_GLOBAL_f32ari64, ----
1360 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_GLOBAL_f64ari64); 0
1361 else ----
1362 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
1363 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_GLOBAL_i8ari64, ----
1364 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_GLOBAL_i16ari64, ----
1365 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_GLOBAL_i32ari64, ----
1366 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_GLOBAL_i64ari64, 0

1374 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2i16_ELE_ari64, ----
1375 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2i32_ELE_ari64, ----
1376 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2i64_ELE_ari64, 0
1377 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2f32_ELE_ari64, ----

1383 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v2i16_ELE_ari64, ----

1432 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2i16_ELE_ari32, ----
1433 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2i32_ELE_ari32, ----
1434 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2i64_ELE_ari32, 0
1435 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2f32_ELE_ari32, ----
1436 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2f64_ELE_ari32); 0
1437 break; 0
1438 case NVPTXISD::LDUV2: 0
1439 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
1440 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v2i8_ELE_ari32, ----
1441 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v2i16_ELE_ari32, ----
1442 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v2i32_ELE_ari32, ----
1443 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v2i64_ELE_ari32, 0
1444 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v2f32_ELE_ari32, ----
1445 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v2f64_ELE_ari32); 0
1446 break; 0
1447 case NVPTXISD::LoadV4: 0
1448 case NVPTXISD::LDGV4: ----
1449 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT( 0
1450 EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v4i8_ELE_ari32, 0
1451 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v4i16_ELE_ari32, ----
1452 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v4i32_ELE_ari32, std::nullopt, ----
1453 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v4f32_ELE_ari32, std::nullopt); ----
1454 break; 0
1455 case NVPTXISD::LDUV4: 0
1456 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT( 0
1457 EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v4i8_ELE_ari32, 0
1458 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v4i16_ELE_ari32, ----
1459 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v4i32_ELE_ari32, std::nullopt, ----
1460 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v4f32_ELE_ari32, std::nullopt); ----
1461 break; 0
1462 } ----
1463 } ----
1464 if (!Opcode) 0
1465 return false; 0
1466 SDValue Ops[] = {Base, Offset, Chain}; 0
1467 LD = CurDAG->getMachineNode(*Opcode, DL, InstVTList, Ops); 0
1468 } else { ----
1469 if (TM.is64Bit()) { 0
1470 switch (N->getOpcode()) { 0
1471 default: 0
1472 return false; 0
1473 case ISD::LOAD: 0
1474 case ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN: ----
1475 if (IsLDG) 0
1476 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
1477 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_GLOBAL_i8areg64, ----
1478 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_GLOBAL_i16areg64, ----
1479 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_GLOBAL_i32areg64, ----
1480 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_GLOBAL_i64areg64, 0
1481 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_GLOBAL_f32areg64, ----
1482 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_GLOBAL_f64areg64); 0
1483 else ----

1485 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_GLOBAL_i8areg64, ----
1486 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_GLOBAL_i16areg64, ----
1487 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_GLOBAL_i32areg64, ----
1488 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_GLOBAL_i64areg64, 0
1489 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_GLOBAL_f32areg64, ----
1490 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_GLOBAL_f64areg64); 0
1491 break; 0
1492 case NVPTXISD::LoadV2: 0
1493 case NVPTXISD::LDGV2: ----
1494 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
1495 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2i8_ELE_areg64, ----
1496 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2i16_ELE_areg64, ----
1497 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2i32_ELE_areg64, ----
1498 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2i64_ELE_areg64, 0
1499 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2f32_ELE_areg64, ----
1500 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2f64_ELE_areg64); 0
1501 break; 0
1502 case NVPTXISD::LDUV2: 0
1503 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
1504 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v2i8_ELE_areg64, ----
1505 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v2i16_ELE_areg64, ----
1506 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v2i32_ELE_areg64, ----
1507 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v2i64_ELE_areg64, 0

1509 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v2f64_ELE_areg64); 0
1510 break; 0

1512 case NVPTXISD::LDGV4: ----
1513 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT( 0
1514 EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v4i8_ELE_areg64, 0
1515 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v4i16_ELE_areg64, ----
1516 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v4i32_ELE_areg64, std::nullopt, ----
1517 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v4f32_ELE_areg64, std::nullopt); ----
1518 break; 0
1519 case NVPTXISD::LDUV4: 0
1520 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT( 0
1521 EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v4i8_ELE_areg64, 0
1522 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v4i16_ELE_areg64, ----
1523 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v4i32_ELE_areg64, std::nullopt, ----
1524 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v4f32_ELE_areg64, std::nullopt); ----
1525 break; 0
1526 } ----
1527 } else { ----
1528 switch (N->getOpcode()) { 0
1529 default: 0
1530 return false; 0
1531 case ISD::LOAD: 0
1532 case ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN: ----
1533 if (IsLDG) 0
1534 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
1535 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_GLOBAL_i8areg, ----
1536 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_GLOBAL_i16areg, ----
1537 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_GLOBAL_i32areg, ----
1538 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_GLOBAL_i64areg, 0
1539 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_GLOBAL_f32areg, ----
1540 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_GLOBAL_f64areg); 0

1543 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_GLOBAL_i8areg, ----
1544 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_GLOBAL_i16areg, ----
1545 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_GLOBAL_i32areg, ----
1546 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_GLOBAL_i64areg, 0
1547 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_GLOBAL_f32areg, ----
1548 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_GLOBAL_f64areg); 0
1549 break; 0
1550 case NVPTXISD::LoadV2: 0
1551 case NVPTXISD::LDGV2: ----
1552 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
1553 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2i8_ELE_areg32, ----
1554 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2i16_ELE_areg32, ----
1555 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2i32_ELE_areg32, ----

1557 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2f32_ELE_areg32, ----
1558 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v2f64_ELE_areg32); 0
1559 break; 0
1560 case NVPTXISD::LDUV2: 0
1561 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
1562 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v2i8_ELE_areg32, ----
1563 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v2i16_ELE_areg32, ----
1564 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v2i32_ELE_areg32, ----
1565 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v2i64_ELE_areg32, 0
1566 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v2f32_ELE_areg32, ----
1567 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v2f64_ELE_areg32); 0
1568 break; 0
1569 case NVPTXISD::LoadV4: 0
1570 case NVPTXISD::LDGV4: ----
1571 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT( 0
1572 EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v4i8_ELE_areg32, 0
1573 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v4i16_ELE_areg32, ----
1574 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v4i32_ELE_areg32, std::nullopt, ----
1575 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDG_G_v4f32_ELE_areg32, std::nullopt); ----
1576 break; 0
1577 case NVPTXISD::LDUV4: 0
1578 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT( 0
1579 EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v4i8_ELE_areg32, 0
1580 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v4i16_ELE_areg32, ----
1581 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v4i32_ELE_areg32, std::nullopt, ----
1582 NVPTX::INT_PTX_LDU_G_v4f32_ELE_areg32, std::nullopt); ----
1583 break; 0
1584 } ----
1585 } ----
1586 if (!Opcode) 0
1587 return false; 0
1588 SDValue Ops[] = { Op1, Chain }; 0
1589 LD = CurDAG->getMachineNode(*Opcode, DL, InstVTList, Ops); 0
1590 } ----
1591 ----
1592 // For automatic generation of LDG (through SelectLoad[Vector], not the ----
1593 // intrinsics), we may have an extending load like: ----
1594 // ----
1595 // i32,ch = load t0, t7, undef:i64 ----
1596 // ----
1597 // In this case, the matching logic above will select a load for the original ----
1598 // memory type (in this case, i8) and our types will not match (the node needs ----
1599 // to return an i32 in this case). Our LDG/LDU nodes do not support the ----
1600 // concept of sign-/zero-extension, so emulate it here by adding an explicit ----
1601 // CVT instruction. Ptxas should clean up any redundancies here. ----
1602 ----
1603 EVT OrigType = N->getValueType(0); 0
1604 LoadSDNode *LdNode = dyn_cast(N); 0
1605 ----
1606 if (OrigType != EltVT && 0
1607 (LdNode || (OrigType.isFloatingPoint() && EltVT.isFloatingPoint()))) { 0
1608 // We have an extending-load. The instruction we selected operates on the ----
1609 // smaller type, but the SDNode we are replacing has the larger type. We ----
1610 // need to emit a CVT to make the types match. ----
1611 unsigned CvtOpc = ----
1612 GetConvertOpcode(OrigType.getSimpleVT(), EltVT.getSimpleVT(), LdNode); 0
1613 ----
1614 // For each output value, apply the manual sign/zero-extension and make sure ----
1615 // all users of the load go through that CVT. ----
1616 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) { 0
1617 SDValue Res(LD, i); 0
1618 SDValue OrigVal(N, i); 0
1619 ----
1620 SDNode *CvtNode = ----
1621 CurDAG->getMachineNode(CvtOpc, DL, OrigType, Res, 0
1622 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(NVPTX::PTXCvtMode::NONE, 0
1623 DL, MVT::i32)); ----
1624 ReplaceUses(OrigVal, SDValue(CvtNode, 0)); 0
1625 } ----
1626 } ----
1627 ----
1628 ReplaceNode(N, LD); 0
1629 return true; 0
1630 } ----
1631 ----
1632 bool NVPTXDAGToDAGISel::tryStore(SDNode *N) { 0
1633 SDLoc dl(N); 0
1634 MemSDNode *ST = cast(N); 0
1635 assert(ST->writeMem() && "Expected store"); 0
1636 StoreSDNode *PlainStore = dyn_cast(N); 0
1637 AtomicSDNode *AtomicStore = dyn_cast(N); 0
1638 assert((PlainStore || AtomicStore) && "Expected store"); 0
1639 EVT StoreVT = ST->getMemoryVT(); 0
1640 SDNode *NVPTXST = nullptr; 0
1641 ----
1642 // do not support pre/post inc/dec ----
1643 if (PlainStore && PlainStore->isIndexed()) 0
1644 return false; 0
1645 ----
1646 if (!StoreVT.isSimple()) 0
1647 return false; 0
1648 ----
1649 AtomicOrdering Ordering = ST->getSuccessOrdering(); 0
1650 // In order to lower atomic loads with stronger guarantees we would need to ----
1651 // use store.release or insert fences. However these features were only added ----
1652 // with PTX ISA 6.0 / sm_70. ----
1653 // TODO: Check if we can actually use the new instructions and implement them. ----
1654 if (isStrongerThanMonotonic(Ordering)) 0
1655 return false; 0
1656 ----
1657 // Address Space Setting ----
1658 unsigned int CodeAddrSpace = getCodeAddrSpace(ST); 0
1659 unsigned int PointerSize = ----
1660 CurDAG->getDataLayout().getPointerSizeInBits(ST->getAddressSpace()); 0
1661 ----
1662 // Volatile Setting ----
1663 // - .volatile is only available for .global and .shared ----
1664 // - .volatile has the same memory synchronization semantics as .relaxed.sys ----
1665 bool isVolatile = ST->isVolatile() || Ordering == AtomicOrdering::Monotonic; 0
1666 if (CodeAddrSpace != NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::GLOBAL && 0
1667 CodeAddrSpace != NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::SHARED && 0
1668 CodeAddrSpace != NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::GENERIC) ----
1669 isVolatile = false; 0
1670 ----
1671 // Vector Setting ----
1672 MVT SimpleVT = StoreVT.getSimpleVT(); 0
1673 unsigned vecType = NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::Scalar; 0
1674 ----
1675 // Type Setting: toType + toTypeWidth ----
1676 // - for integer type, always use 'u' ----
1677 // ----
1678 MVT ScalarVT = SimpleVT.getScalarType(); 0
1679 unsigned toTypeWidth = ScalarVT.getSizeInBits(); 0
1680 if (SimpleVT.isVector()) { 0
1681 assert((StoreVT == MVT::v2f16 || StoreVT == MVT::v2bf16) && 0
1682 "Unexpected vector type"); ----
1683 // v2f16 is stored using st.b32 ----
1684 toTypeWidth = 32; 0
1685 } ----
1686 ----
1687 unsigned int toType = getLdStRegType(ScalarVT); 0
1688 ----
1689 // Create the machine instruction DAG ----
1690 SDValue Chain = ST->getChain(); 0
1691 SDValue Value = PlainStore ? PlainStore->getValue() : AtomicStore->getVal(); 0
1692 SDValue BasePtr = ST->getBasePtr(); 0
1693 SDValue Addr; 0
1694 SDValue Offset, Base; 0
1695 std::optional Opcode; 0
1696 MVT::SimpleValueType SourceVT = ----
1697 Value.getNode()->getSimpleValueType(0).SimpleTy; 0
1698 ----
1699 if (SelectDirectAddr(BasePtr, Addr)) { 0
1700 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(SourceVT, NVPTX::ST_i8_avar, NVPTX::ST_i16_avar, 0
1701 NVPTX::ST_i32_avar, NVPTX::ST_i64_avar, 0
1702 NVPTX::ST_f32_avar, NVPTX::ST_f64_avar); 0
1703 if (!Opcode) 0
1704 return false; 0
1705 SDValue Ops[] = {Value, ----
1706 getI32Imm(isVolatile, dl), 0
1707 getI32Imm(CodeAddrSpace, dl), 0
1708 getI32Imm(vecType, dl), 0
1709 getI32Imm(toType, dl), 0
1710 getI32Imm(toTypeWidth, dl), 0
1711 Addr, ----
1712 Chain}; 0
1713 NVPTXST = CurDAG->getMachineNode(*Opcode, dl, MVT::Other, Ops); 0
1714 } else if (PointerSize == 64 0
1715 ? SelectADDRsi64(BasePtr.getNode(), BasePtr, Base, Offset) 0
1716 : SelectADDRsi(BasePtr.getNode(), BasePtr, Base, Offset)) { 0
1717 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(SourceVT, NVPTX::ST_i8_asi, NVPTX::ST_i16_asi, 0
1718 NVPTX::ST_i32_asi, NVPTX::ST_i64_asi, 0
1719 NVPTX::ST_f32_asi, NVPTX::ST_f64_asi); 0
1720 if (!Opcode) 0
1721 return false; 0
1722 SDValue Ops[] = {Value, ----
1723 getI32Imm(isVolatile, dl), 0
1724 getI32Imm(CodeAddrSpace, dl), 0
1725 getI32Imm(vecType, dl), 0
1726 getI32Imm(toType, dl), 0
1727 getI32Imm(toTypeWidth, dl), 0
1728 Base, ----
1729 Offset, ----
1730 Chain}; 0
1731 NVPTXST = CurDAG->getMachineNode(*Opcode, dl, MVT::Other, Ops); 0
1732 } else if (PointerSize == 64 0
1733 ? SelectADDRri64(BasePtr.getNode(), BasePtr, Base, Offset) 0
1734 : SelectADDRri(BasePtr.getNode(), BasePtr, Base, Offset)) { 0
1735 if (PointerSize == 64) 0
1736 Opcode = ----
1737 pickOpcodeForVT(SourceVT, NVPTX::ST_i8_ari_64, NVPTX::ST_i16_ari_64, 0
1738 NVPTX::ST_i32_ari_64, NVPTX::ST_i64_ari_64, 0
1739 NVPTX::ST_f32_ari_64, NVPTX::ST_f64_ari_64); 0
1740 else ----
1741 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(SourceVT, NVPTX::ST_i8_ari, NVPTX::ST_i16_ari, 0
1742 NVPTX::ST_i32_ari, NVPTX::ST_i64_ari, 0
1743 NVPTX::ST_f32_ari, NVPTX::ST_f64_ari); 0
1744 if (!Opcode) 0
1745 return false; 0
1746 ----
1747 SDValue Ops[] = {Value, ----
1748 getI32Imm(isVolatile, dl), 0
1749 getI32Imm(CodeAddrSpace, dl), 0
1750 getI32Imm(vecType, dl), 0
1751 getI32Imm(toType, dl), 0
1752 getI32Imm(toTypeWidth, dl), 0
1753 Base, ----
1754 Offset, ----
1755 Chain}; 0
1756 NVPTXST = CurDAG->getMachineNode(*Opcode, dl, MVT::Other, Ops); 0
1757 } else { ----
1758 if (PointerSize == 64) 0
1759 Opcode = ----
1760 pickOpcodeForVT(SourceVT, NVPTX::ST_i8_areg_64, NVPTX::ST_i16_areg_64, 0
1761 NVPTX::ST_i32_areg_64, NVPTX::ST_i64_areg_64, 0
1762 NVPTX::ST_f32_areg_64, NVPTX::ST_f64_areg_64); 0
1763 else ----
1764 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(SourceVT, NVPTX::ST_i8_areg, NVPTX::ST_i16_areg, 0
1765 NVPTX::ST_i32_areg, NVPTX::ST_i64_areg, 0
1766 NVPTX::ST_f32_areg, NVPTX::ST_f64_areg); 0
1767 if (!Opcode) 0
1768 return false; 0
1769 SDValue Ops[] = {Value, ----
1770 getI32Imm(isVolatile, dl), 0
1771 getI32Imm(CodeAddrSpace, dl), 0
1772 getI32Imm(vecType, dl), 0
1773 getI32Imm(toType, dl), 0
1774 getI32Imm(toTypeWidth, dl), 0
1775 BasePtr, ----
1776 Chain}; 0
1777 NVPTXST = CurDAG->getMachineNode(*Opcode, dl, MVT::Other, Ops); 0
1778 } ----
1779 ----
1780 if (!NVPTXST) 0
1781 return false; 0
1782 ----
1783 MachineMemOperand *MemRef = cast(N)->getMemOperand(); 0
1784 CurDAG->setNodeMemRefs(cast(NVPTXST), {MemRef}); 0
1785 ReplaceNode(N, NVPTXST); 0
1786 return true; 0
1787 } 0
1788 ----
1789 bool NVPTXDAGToDAGISel::tryStoreVector(SDNode *N) { 0
1790 SDValue Chain = N->getOperand(0); 0
1791 SDValue Op1 = N->getOperand(1); 0
1792 SDValue Addr, Offset, Base; 0
1793 std::optional Opcode; 0
1794 SDLoc DL(N); 0
1795 SDNode *ST; ----
1796 EVT EltVT = Op1.getValueType(); 0
1797 MemSDNode *MemSD = cast(N); 0
1798 EVT StoreVT = MemSD->getMemoryVT(); 0
1799 ----
1800 // Address Space Setting ----
1801 unsigned CodeAddrSpace = getCodeAddrSpace(MemSD); 0
1802 if (CodeAddrSpace == NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::CONSTANT) { 0
1803 report_fatal_error("Cannot store to pointer that points to constant " 0
1804 "memory space"); ----
1805 } ----
1806 unsigned int PointerSize = ----
1807 CurDAG->getDataLayout().getPointerSizeInBits(MemSD->getAddressSpace()); 0
1808 ----
1809 // Volatile Setting ----
1810 // - .volatile is only availalble for .global and .shared ----
1811 bool IsVolatile = MemSD->isVolatile(); 0
1812 if (CodeAddrSpace != NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::GLOBAL && 0
1813 CodeAddrSpace != NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::SHARED && 0
1814 CodeAddrSpace != NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::GENERIC) ----
1815 IsVolatile = false; 0
1816 ----
1817 // Type Setting: toType + toTypeWidth ----
1818 // - for integer type, always use 'u' ----
1819 assert(StoreVT.isSimple() && "Store value is not simple"); 0
1820 MVT ScalarVT = StoreVT.getSimpleVT().getScalarType(); 0
1821 unsigned ToTypeWidth = ScalarVT.getSizeInBits(); 0
1822 unsigned ToType = getLdStRegType(ScalarVT); 0
1823 ----
1824 SmallVector StOps; 0
1825 SDValue N2; 0
1826 unsigned VecType; ----
1827 ----
1828 switch (N->getOpcode()) { 0
1829 case NVPTXISD::StoreV2: 0
1830 VecType = NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::V2; 0
1831 StOps.push_back(N->getOperand(1)); 0
1832 StOps.push_back(N->getOperand(2)); 0
1833 N2 = N->getOperand(3); 0
1834 break; 0
1835 case NVPTXISD::StoreV4: 0
1836 VecType = NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::V4; 0
1837 StOps.push_back(N->getOperand(1)); 0
1838 StOps.push_back(N->getOperand(2)); 0
1839 StOps.push_back(N->getOperand(3)); 0
1840 StOps.push_back(N->getOperand(4)); 0
1841 N2 = N->getOperand(5); 0
1842 break; 0
1843 default: 0
1844 return false; 0
1845 } ----
1846 ----
1847 // v8f16 is a special case. PTX doesn't have st.v8.f16 ----
1848 // instruction. Instead, we split the vector into v2f16 chunks and ----
1849 // store them with st.v4.b32. ----
1850 if (EltVT == MVT::v2f16 || EltVT == MVT::v2bf16) { 0
1851 assert(N->getOpcode() == NVPTXISD::StoreV4 && "Unexpected load opcode."); 0
1852 EltVT = MVT::i32; 0
1853 ToType = NVPTX::PTXLdStInstCode::Untyped; 0
1854 ToTypeWidth = 32; 0
1855 } ----
1856 ----
1857 StOps.push_back(getI32Imm(IsVolatile, DL)); 0
1858 StOps.push_back(getI32Imm(CodeAddrSpace, DL)); 0
1859 StOps.push_back(getI32Imm(VecType, DL)); 0
1860 StOps.push_back(getI32Imm(ToType, DL)); 0
1861 StOps.push_back(getI32Imm(ToTypeWidth, DL)); 0
1862 ----
1863 if (SelectDirectAddr(N2, Addr)) { 0
1864 switch (N->getOpcode()) { 0
1865 default: 0
1866 return false; 0
1867 case NVPTXISD::StoreV2: 0
1868 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
1869 NVPTX::STV_i8_v2_avar, NVPTX::STV_i16_v2_avar, ----
1870 NVPTX::STV_i32_v2_avar, NVPTX::STV_i64_v2_avar, 0
1871 NVPTX::STV_f32_v2_avar, NVPTX::STV_f64_v2_avar); 0
1872 break; 0
1873 case NVPTXISD::StoreV4: 0
1874 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(EltVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
1875 NVPTX::STV_i8_v4_avar, NVPTX::STV_i16_v4_avar, ----
1876 NVPTX::STV_i32_v4_avar, std::nullopt, ----
1877 NVPTX::STV_f32_v4_avar, std::nullopt); ----
1878 break; 0
1879 } ----
1880 StOps.push_back(Addr); 0

1995 ----
1996 bool NVPTXDAGToDAGISel::tryLoadParam(SDNode *Node) { 0
1997 SDValue Chain = Node->getOperand(0); 0
1998 SDValue Offset = Node->getOperand(2); 0
1999 SDValue Glue = Node->getOperand(3); 0
2000 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
2001 MemSDNode *Mem = cast(Node); 0
2002 ----
2003 unsigned VecSize; ----
2004 switch (Node->getOpcode()) { 0
2005 default: 0
2006 return false; 0
2007 case NVPTXISD::LoadParam: 0
2008 VecSize = 1; 0
2009 break; 0
2010 case NVPTXISD::LoadParamV2: 0
2011 VecSize = 2; 0
2012 break; 0
2013 case NVPTXISD::LoadParamV4: 0
2014 VecSize = 4; 0
2015 break; 0
2016 } ----
2017 ----
2018 EVT EltVT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
2019 EVT MemVT = Mem->getMemoryVT(); 0
2020 ----
2021 std::optional Opcode; 0
2022 ----
2023 switch (VecSize) { 0
2024 default: 0
2025 return false; 0
2026 case 1: 0
2027 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(MemVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
2028 NVPTX::LoadParamMemI8, NVPTX::LoadParamMemI16, ----
2029 NVPTX::LoadParamMemI32, NVPTX::LoadParamMemI64, 0
2030 NVPTX::LoadParamMemF32, NVPTX::LoadParamMemF64); 0
2031 break; 0
2032 case 2: 0
2033 Opcode = ----
2034 pickOpcodeForVT(MemVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, NVPTX::LoadParamMemV2I8, 0
2035 NVPTX::LoadParamMemV2I16, NVPTX::LoadParamMemV2I32, ----
2036 NVPTX::LoadParamMemV2I64, NVPTX::LoadParamMemV2F32, 0
2037 NVPTX::LoadParamMemV2F64); 0
2038 break; 0
2039 case 4: 0
2040 Opcode = ----
2041 pickOpcodeForVT(MemVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, NVPTX::LoadParamMemV4I8, 0
2042 NVPTX::LoadParamMemV4I16, NVPTX::LoadParamMemV4I32, ----
2043 std::nullopt, NVPTX::LoadParamMemV4F32, std::nullopt); ----
2044 break; 0
2045 } ----
2046 if (!Opcode) 0
2047 return false; 0
2048 ----
2049 SDVTList VTs; ----
2050 if (VecSize == 1) { 0
2051 VTs = CurDAG->getVTList(EltVT, MVT::Other, MVT::Glue); 0
2052 } else if (VecSize == 2) { 0
2053 VTs = CurDAG->getVTList(EltVT, EltVT, MVT::Other, MVT::Glue); 0
2054 } else { ----
2055 EVT EVTs[] = { EltVT, EltVT, EltVT, EltVT, MVT::Other, MVT::Glue }; 0
2056 VTs = CurDAG->getVTList(EVTs); 0
2057 } ----
2058 ----
2059 unsigned OffsetVal = cast(Offset)->getZExtValue(); 0
2060 ----
2061 SmallVector Ops; 0
2062 Ops.push_back(CurDAG->getTargetConstant(OffsetVal, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
2063 Ops.push_back(Chain); 0
2064 Ops.push_back(Glue); 0
2065 ----
2066 ReplaceNode(Node, CurDAG->getMachineNode(*Opcode, DL, VTs, Ops)); 0
2067 return true; 0
2068 } 0

2070 bool NVPTXDAGToDAGISel::tryStoreRetval(SDNode *N) { 0
2071 SDLoc DL(N); 0
2072 SDValue Chain = N->getOperand(0); 0
2073 SDValue Offset = N->getOperand(1); 0
2074 unsigned OffsetVal = cast(Offset)->getZExtValue(); 0
2075 MemSDNode *Mem = cast(N); 0
2076 ----
2077 // How many elements do we have? ----
2078 unsigned NumElts = 1; 0
2079 switch (N->getOpcode()) { 0
2080 default: 0
2081 return false; 0
2082 case NVPTXISD::StoreRetval: 0
2083 NumElts = 1; 0
2084 break; 0
2085 case NVPTXISD::StoreRetvalV2: 0
2086 NumElts = 2; 0
2087 break; 0
2088 case NVPTXISD::StoreRetvalV4: 0
2089 NumElts = 4; 0
2090 break; 0
2091 } ----
2092 ----
2093 // Build vector of operands ----
2094 SmallVector Ops; 0
2095 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumElts; ++i) 0
2096 Ops.push_back(N->getOperand(i + 2)); 0
2097 Ops.push_back(CurDAG->getTargetConstant(OffsetVal, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
2098 Ops.push_back(Chain); 0
2099 ----
2100 // Determine target opcode ----
2101 // If we have an i1, use an 8-bit store. The lowering code in ----
2102 // NVPTXISelLowering will have already emitted an upcast. ----
2103 std::optional Opcode = 0; 0
2104 switch (NumElts) { 0
2105 default: 0
2106 return false; 0
2107 case 1: 0
2108 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(Mem->getMemoryVT().getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
2109 NVPTX::StoreRetvalI8, NVPTX::StoreRetvalI16, ----
2110 NVPTX::StoreRetvalI32, NVPTX::StoreRetvalI64, 0
2111 NVPTX::StoreRetvalF32, NVPTX::StoreRetvalF64); 0
2112 break; 0
2113 case 2: 0
2114 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(Mem->getMemoryVT().getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
2115 NVPTX::StoreRetvalV2I8, NVPTX::StoreRetvalV2I16, ----
2116 NVPTX::StoreRetvalV2I32, NVPTX::StoreRetvalV2I64, 0
2117 NVPTX::StoreRetvalV2F32, NVPTX::StoreRetvalV2F64); 0
2118 break; 0
2119 case 4: 0
2120 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(Mem->getMemoryVT().getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
2121 NVPTX::StoreRetvalV4I8, NVPTX::StoreRetvalV4I16, ----
2122 NVPTX::StoreRetvalV4I32, std::nullopt, ----
2123 NVPTX::StoreRetvalV4F32, std::nullopt); ----
2124 break; 0
2125 } ----
2126 if (!Opcode) 0
2127 return false; 0
2128 ----
2129 SDNode *Ret = CurDAG->getMachineNode(*Opcode, DL, MVT::Other, Ops); 0
2130 MachineMemOperand *MemRef = cast(N)->getMemOperand(); 0
2131 CurDAG->setNodeMemRefs(cast(Ret), {MemRef}); 0
2132 ----
2133 ReplaceNode(N, Ret); 0
2134 return true; 0
2135 } 0
2136 ----
2137 bool NVPTXDAGToDAGISel::tryStoreParam(SDNode *N) { 0
2138 SDLoc DL(N); 0
2139 SDValue Chain = N->getOperand(0); 0
2140 SDValue Param = N->getOperand(1); 0
2141 unsigned ParamVal = cast(Param)->getZExtValue(); 0
2142 SDValue Offset = N->getOperand(2); 0
2143 unsigned OffsetVal = cast(Offset)->getZExtValue(); 0
2144 MemSDNode *Mem = cast(N); 0
2145 SDValue Glue = N->getOperand(N->getNumOperands() - 1); 0
2146 ----
2147 // How many elements do we have? ----
2148 unsigned NumElts = 1; 0
2149 switch (N->getOpcode()) { 0
2150 default: 0
2151 return false; 0
2152 case NVPTXISD::StoreParamU32: 0
2153 case NVPTXISD::StoreParamS32: ----
2154 case NVPTXISD::StoreParam: ----
2155 NumElts = 1; 0
2156 break; 0
2157 case NVPTXISD::StoreParamV2: 0
2158 NumElts = 2; 0
2159 break; 0
2160 case NVPTXISD::StoreParamV4: 0
2161 NumElts = 4; 0
2162 break; 0
2163 } ----
2164 ----
2165 // Build vector of operands ----
2166 SmallVector Ops; 0
2167 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumElts; ++i) 0
2168 Ops.push_back(N->getOperand(i + 3)); 0
2169 Ops.push_back(CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ParamVal, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
2170 Ops.push_back(CurDAG->getTargetConstant(OffsetVal, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
2171 Ops.push_back(Chain); 0
2172 Ops.push_back(Glue); 0
2173 ----
2174 // Determine target opcode ----
2175 // If we have an i1, use an 8-bit store. The lowering code in ----
2176 // NVPTXISelLowering will have already emitted an upcast. ----
2177 std::optional Opcode = 0; 0
2178 switch (N->getOpcode()) { 0
2179 default: 0
2180 switch (NumElts) { ----
2181 default: 0
2182 return false; 0
2183 case 1: 0
2184 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(Mem->getMemoryVT().getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
2185 NVPTX::StoreParamI8, NVPTX::StoreParamI16, ----
2186 NVPTX::StoreParamI32, NVPTX::StoreParamI64, 0
2187 NVPTX::StoreParamF32, NVPTX::StoreParamF64); 0
2188 break; 0
2189 case 2: 0
2190 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(Mem->getMemoryVT().getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
2191 NVPTX::StoreParamV2I8, NVPTX::StoreParamV2I16, ----
2192 NVPTX::StoreParamV2I32, NVPTX::StoreParamV2I64, 0
2193 NVPTX::StoreParamV2F32, NVPTX::StoreParamV2F64); 0
2194 break; 0
2195 case 4: 0
2196 Opcode = pickOpcodeForVT(Mem->getMemoryVT().getSimpleVT().SimpleTy, 0
2197 NVPTX::StoreParamV4I8, NVPTX::StoreParamV4I16, ----
2198 NVPTX::StoreParamV4I32, std::nullopt, ----
2199 NVPTX::StoreParamV4F32, std::nullopt); ----
2200 break; 0
2201 } ----
2202 if (!Opcode) 0
2203 return false; 0
2204 break; 0
2205 // Special case: if we have a sign-extend/zero-extend node, insert the ----
2206 // conversion instruction first, and use that as the value operand to ----
2207 // the selected StoreParam node. ----
2208 case NVPTXISD::StoreParamU32: { 0
2209 Opcode = NVPTX::StoreParamI32; 0
2210 SDValue CvtNone = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(NVPTX::PTXCvtMode::NONE, DL, 0
2211 MVT::i32); ----
2212 SDNode *Cvt = CurDAG->getMachineNode(NVPTX::CVT_u32_u16, DL, 0
2213 MVT::i32, Ops[0], CvtNone); 0
2214 Ops[0] = SDValue(Cvt, 0); 0
2215 break; 0
2216 } ----
2217 case NVPTXISD::StoreParamS32: { 0
2218 Opcode = NVPTX::StoreParamI32; 0
2219 SDValue CvtNone = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(NVPTX::PTXCvtMode::NONE, DL, 0
2220 MVT::i32); ----
2221 SDNode *Cvt = CurDAG->getMachineNode(NVPTX::CVT_s32_s16, DL, 0
2222 MVT::i32, Ops[0], CvtNone); 0
2223 Ops[0] = SDValue(Cvt, 0); 0
2224 break; 0
2225 } ----
2226 } ----
2227 ----
2228 SDVTList RetVTs = CurDAG->getVTList(MVT::Other, MVT::Glue); 0
2229 SDNode *Ret = CurDAG->getMachineNode(*Opcode, DL, RetVTs, Ops); 0
2230 MachineMemOperand *MemRef = cast(N)->getMemOperand(); 0
2231 CurDAG->setNodeMemRefs(cast(Ret), {MemRef}); 0
2232 ----
2233 ReplaceNode(N, Ret); 0
2234 return true; 0
2235 } 0

3266 /// SelectBFE - Look for instruction sequences that can be made more efficient ----
3267 /// by using the 'bfe' (bit-field extract) PTX instruction ----
3268 bool NVPTXDAGToDAGISel::tryBFE(SDNode *N) { 0
3269 SDLoc DL(N); 0
3270 SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0); 0
3271 SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1); 0
3272 SDValue Len; 0
3273 SDValue Start; 0
3274 SDValue Val; 0
3275 bool IsSigned = false; 0
3276 ----
3277 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::AND) { 0
3278 // Canonicalize the operands ----
3279 // We want 'and %val, %mask' ----
3280 if (isa(LHS) && !isa(RHS)) { 0
3281 std::swap(LHS, RHS); 0
3282 } ----
3283 ----
3284 ConstantSDNode *Mask = dyn_cast(RHS); 0
3285 if (!Mask) { 0
3286 // We need a constant mask on the RHS of the AND ----
3287 return false; 0
3288 } ----
3289 ----
3290 // Extract the mask bits ----
3291 uint64_t MaskVal = Mask->getZExtValue(); 0
3292 if (!isMask_64(MaskVal)) { 0
3293 // We *could* handle shifted masks here, but doing so would require an ----
3294 // 'and' operation to fix up the low-order bits so we would trade ----
3295 // shr+and for bfe+and, which has the same throughput ----
3296 return false; 0
3297 } ----
3298 ----
3299 // How many bits are in our mask? ----
3300 int64_t NumBits = countr_one(MaskVal); 0
3301 Len = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(NumBits, DL, MVT::i32); 0
3302 ----
3303 if (LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SRL || LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SRA) { 0
3304 // We have a 'srl/and' pair, extract the effective start bit and length ----
3305 Val = LHS.getNode()->getOperand(0); 0
3306 Start = LHS.getNode()->getOperand(1); 0
3307 ConstantSDNode *StartConst = dyn_cast(Start); 0
3308 if (StartConst) { 0
3309 uint64_t StartVal = StartConst->getZExtValue(); 0
3310 // How many "good" bits do we have left? "good" is defined here as bits ----
3311 // that exist in the original value, not shifted in. ----
3312 int64_t GoodBits = Start.getValueSizeInBits() - StartVal; 0
3313 if (NumBits > GoodBits) { 0
3314 // Do not handle the case where bits have been shifted in. In theory ----
3315 // we could handle this, but the cost is likely higher than just ----
3316 // emitting the srl/and pair. ----
3317 return false; 0
3318 } ----
3319 Start = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(StartVal, DL, MVT::i32); 0
3320 } else { ----
3321 // Do not handle the case where the shift amount (can be zero if no srl ----
3322 // was found) is not constant. We could handle this case, but it would ----
3323 // require run-time logic that would be more expensive than just ----
3324 // emitting the srl/and pair. ----
3325 return false; 0
3326 } ----
3327 } else { ----
3328 // Do not handle the case where the LHS of the and is not a shift. While ----
3329 // it would be trivial to handle this case, it would just transform ----
3330 // 'and' -> 'bfe', but 'and' has higher-throughput. ----
3331 return false; 0
3332 } ----
3333 } else if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::SRL || N->getOpcode() == ISD::SRA) { 0
3334 if (LHS->getOpcode() == ISD::AND) { 0
3335 ConstantSDNode *ShiftCnst = dyn_cast(RHS); 0
3336 if (!ShiftCnst) { 0
3337 // Shift amount must be constant ----
3338 return false; 0
3339 } ----
3340 ----
3341 uint64_t ShiftAmt = ShiftCnst->getZExtValue(); 0
3342 ----
3343 SDValue AndLHS = LHS->getOperand(0); 0
3344 SDValue AndRHS = LHS->getOperand(1); 0
3345 ----
3346 // Canonicalize the AND to have the mask on the RHS ----
3347 if (isa(AndLHS)) { 0
3348 std::swap(AndLHS, AndRHS); 0
3349 } ----
3350 ----
3351 ConstantSDNode *MaskCnst = dyn_cast(AndRHS); 0
3352 if (!MaskCnst) { 0
3353 // Mask must be constant ----
3354 return false; 0
3355 } ----
3356 ----
3357 uint64_t MaskVal = MaskCnst->getZExtValue(); 0
3358 uint64_t NumZeros; ----
3359 uint64_t NumBits; ----
3360 if (isMask_64(MaskVal)) { 0
3361 NumZeros = 0; 0
3362 // The number of bits in the result bitfield will be the number of ----
3363 // trailing ones (the AND) minus the number of bits we shift off ----
3364 NumBits = llvm::countr_one(MaskVal) - ShiftAmt; 0
3365 } else if (isShiftedMask_64(MaskVal)) { 0
3366 NumZeros = llvm::countr_zero(MaskVal); 0
3367 unsigned NumOnes = llvm::countr_one(MaskVal >> NumZeros); 0
3368 // The number of bits in the result bitfield will be the number of ----
3369 // trailing zeros plus the number of set bits in the mask minus the ----
3370 // number of bits we shift off ----
3371 NumBits = NumZeros + NumOnes - ShiftAmt; 0
3372 } else { ----
3373 // This is not a mask we can handle ----
3374 return false; 0
3375 } ----
3376 ----
3377 if (ShiftAmt < NumZeros) { 0
3378 // Handling this case would require extra logic that would make this ----
3379 // transformation non-profitable ----
3380 return false; 0
3381 } ----
3382 ----
3383 Val = AndLHS; 0
3384 Start = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ShiftAmt, DL, MVT::i32); 0
3385 Len = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(NumBits, DL, MVT::i32); 0
3386 } else if (LHS->getOpcode() == ISD::SHL) { 0
3387 // Here, we have a pattern like: ----
3388 // ----
3389 // (sra (shl val, NN), MM) ----
3390 // or ----
3391 // (srl (shl val, NN), MM) ----
3392 // ----
3393 // If MM >= NN, we can efficiently optimize this with bfe ----
3394 Val = LHS->getOperand(0); 0
3395 ----
3396 SDValue ShlRHS = LHS->getOperand(1); 0
3397 ConstantSDNode *ShlCnst = dyn_cast(ShlRHS); 0
3398 if (!ShlCnst) { 0
3399 // Shift amount must be constant ----
3400 return false; 0
3401 } ----
3402 uint64_t InnerShiftAmt = ShlCnst->getZExtValue(); 0
3403 ----
3404 SDValue ShrRHS = RHS; 0
3405 ConstantSDNode *ShrCnst = dyn_cast(ShrRHS); 0
3406 if (!ShrCnst) { 0
3407 // Shift amount must be constant ----
3408 return false; 0
3409 } ----
3410 uint64_t OuterShiftAmt = ShrCnst->getZExtValue(); 0
3411 ----
3412 // To avoid extra codegen and be profitable, we need Outer >= Inner ----
3413 if (OuterShiftAmt < InnerShiftAmt) { 0
3414 return false; 0
3415 } ----
3416 ----
3417 // If the outer shift is more than the type size, we have no bitfield to ----
3418 // extract (since we also check that the inner shift is <= the outer shift ----
3419 // then this also implies that the inner shift is < the type size) ----
3420 if (OuterShiftAmt >= Val.getValueSizeInBits()) { 0
3421 return false; 0
3422 } ----
3423 ----
3424 Start = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(OuterShiftAmt - InnerShiftAmt, DL, 0
3425 MVT::i32); ----
3426 Len = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Val.getValueSizeInBits() - OuterShiftAmt, 0
3427 DL, MVT::i32); ----
3428 ----
3429 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::SRA) { 0
3430 // If we have a arithmetic right shift, we need to use the signed bfe ----
3431 // variant ----
3432 IsSigned = true; 0
3433 } ----
3434 } else { ----
3435 // No can do... ----
3436 return false; 0
3437 } ----
3438 } else { ----
3439 // No can do... ----
3440 return false; 0
3441 } ----
3442 ----
3443 ----
3444 unsigned Opc; ----
3445 // For the BFE operations we form here from "and" and "srl", always use the ----
3446 // unsigned variants. ----
3447 if (Val.getValueType() == MVT::i32) { 0
3448 if (IsSigned) { 0
3449 Opc = NVPTX::BFE_S32rii; 0
3450 } else { ----
3451 Opc = NVPTX::BFE_U32rii; 0
3452 } ----
3453 } else if (Val.getValueType() == MVT::i64) { 0
3454 if (IsSigned) { 0
3455 Opc = NVPTX::BFE_S64rii; 0
3456 } else { ----
3457 Opc = NVPTX::BFE_U64rii; 0
3458 } ----
3459 } else { ----
3460 // We cannot handle this type ----
3461 return false; 0
3462 } ----
3463 ----
3464 SDValue Ops[] = { ----
3465 Val, Start, Len ----
3466 }; 0
3467 ----
3468 ReplaceNode(N, CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opc, DL, N->getVTList(), Ops)); 0
3469 return true; 0
3470 } 0

3473 // A direct address could be a globaladdress or externalsymbol. ----
3474 bool NVPTXDAGToDAGISel::SelectDirectAddr(SDValue N, SDValue &Address) { 0
3475 // Return true if TGA or ES. ----
3476 if (N.getOpcode() == ISD::TargetGlobalAddress || 0
3477 N.getOpcode() == ISD::TargetExternalSymbol) { 0
3478 Address = N; 0
3479 return true; 0
3480 } ----
3481 if (N.getOpcode() == NVPTXISD::Wrapper) { 0
3482 Address = N.getOperand(0); 0
3483 return true; 0
3484 } ----

3489 CastN->getOperand(0).getOpcode() == NVPTXISD::MoveParam) 0
3490 return SelectDirectAddr(CastN->getOperand(0).getOperand(0), Address); 0
3491 } ----
3492 return false; 0
3493 } ----
